    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_005/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "FGSEA (Fast Gene Set Enrichment Analysis) method that is able to estimate arbitrarily low GSEA P-values with a high accuracy in a matter of minutes or even seconds. To confirm the accuracy of the method, we also developed an exact algorithm for GSEA P-values calculation for integer gene-level statistics.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms fgsea estimates P-values with high accuracy and mentions an exact algorithm for P-value calculation, but does not explicitly name or describe the 'adaptive multi-level split Monte-Carlo scheme' or discuss the eps parameter behavior. The research question's specific technical mechanism (adaptive multi-level split MCMC, eps parameter tuning) is not verbatim in passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1101-060012",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_005",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the adaptive multi-level split Monte-Carlo scheme in fgsea adjust P-value precision when the eps parameter is set to zero rather than using a default lower-bound threshold?",
